<subSubSection id="93B1A215AFC2FE5409F8483DA5DBBB32" pageId="0" pageNumber="33" type="notes">
<paragraph id="FA680635D3CDD2087136E4850DD3C71A" pageId="0" pageNumber="33">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="041EFE4FFD1F47C88AA7464E7C4C16ED" pageId="0" pageNumber="33">
Type material for the varietal names coined by Georg Bitter in the original publication of 
<taxonomicName id="CE331E4E56126BB61361BD6C134EEDA5" genus="S." lsidName="S. physalidicalyx" pageId="0" pageNumber="33" rank="species" species="physalidicalyx">
<emphasis id="217427AE90088B2D364E5F53A2D782BC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="33">S. physalidicalyx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="D36A64D601FDD81F4FD0333EA3D795D4" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1002/fedr.19120110917" author="Bitter, G" journalOrPublisher="Repertorium Specierum Novarum Regni Vegetabilis" pageId="0" pageNumber="33" pagination="202 - 237" refId="B4" refString="Bitter, G, 1912. Solana nova vel minus cognita. III. Repertorium Specierum Novarum Regni Vegetabilis 11 (9-15): 202 - 237, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1002/fedr.19120110917" title="Solana nova vel minus cognita. III." url="https://doi.org/10.1002/fedr.19120110917" volume="11" year="1912">Bitter 1912</bibRefCitation>
) may correspond to duplicates of the type collection of the species itself, making all three names homotypic. In describing var. 
<taxonomicName id="41F55028326E6506C3AE9A7D42728D1E" genus="S." lsidName="var. integrascens" pageId="0" pageNumber="33" rank="variety" species="physalidicalyx" variety="integrascens">integrascens</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation id="1E88EF9087592052582A3C8BD75DEC5A" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1002/fedr.19120110917" author="Bitter, G" journalOrPublisher="Repertorium Specierum Novarum Regni Vegetabilis" pageId="0" pageNumber="33" pagination="202 - 237" refId="B4" refString="Bitter, G, 1912. Solana nova vel minus cognita. III. Repertorium Specierum Novarum Regni Vegetabilis 11 (9-15): 202 - 237, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1002/fedr.19120110917" title="Solana nova vel minus cognita. III." url="https://doi.org/10.1002/fedr.19120110917" volume="11" year="1912">Bitter (1912)</bibRefCitation>
states &quot;var. integrifolia quod in descriptione specie pro typo habui&quot; [var. integrifolia I had in the description of the type of the species] suggesting this name at least is based on 
<emphasis id="365DA1AE7D5BC4D1D2429126480DA6AF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="33">Lorentz &amp; Hieronymus 364</emphasis>
. Bitter often used duplicates with minor leaf variations as material for describing infraspecific variation (
<bibRefCitation id="CE76679FCB89EFE3F456A647E40E33F7" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.22.4041" author="Knapp, S" journalOrPublisher="PhytoKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="33" pagination="1 - 432" refId="B10" refString="Knapp, S, 2013. A revision of the Dulcamaroid clade of Solanum L. (Solanaceae). PhytoKeys 22 (0): 1 - 432, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.22.4041" title="A revision of the Dulcamaroid clade of Solanum L. (Solanaceae)." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.22.4041" volume="22" year="2013">Knapp 2013</bibRefCitation>
). None of the duplicates of these Lorentz and Hieronymus collections from Salta have annotations in 
<normalizedToken id="614CEA4AAD8A7B23ACF15F3FE952F8FA" originalValue="Bitter’s">Bitter's</normalizedToken>
hand, and we have found no other collections of 
<taxonomicName id="6A2D57679C7B549AE4979F66EA6E7A1D" genus="S." lsidName="S. physalidicalyx" pageId="0" pageNumber="33" rank="species" species="physalidicalyx">
<emphasis id="97225B83CCA53A1E62E9C666436D9134" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="33">S. physalidicalyx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
made by Lorentz and Hieronymus from &quot;Pasaje de Juramento&quot;.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
